description: {"blocks":[{"key":"2pa8d","text":"The gp32 is a single strand binding protein (SSB) that plays a role in genetic recombination, replication and repair from the bacteriophage T4. The gp32 is used as part of an isothermal DNA amplification based on the recombination process, the RPA reaction. RPA uses 4 enzymes: UvsX, UvsY, Bsu and Gp32. It's an isothermal amplification technique that can run at 37°C. In this protocol we are producing a recombinant gp32 that has a 6xHIS-tag using a E. coli  expression system. The protocols for the production of the other proteins are also available in protocols.io.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
